items.synopsis: Australia's under-pressure banks unveil a new tool to combat fraudulent transactions, in a bid to stop customers losing more and more money to sophisticated scams.

title.children: Banks launch new weapon to help recover scam victims' money

image.altText: A Red Rooster store and a Cold Rock store

items.synopsis: Two Victorian fast-food businesses are hit with hundreds of charges for allegedly failing to comply with child labour laws, as the state's watchdog cracks down on hospitality and retail franchises.

title.children: Red Rooster and Cold Rock franchisees hit with hundreds of charges for allegedly failing to comply with child labour laws

image.altText: Sunak and Zelenskyy look at each other in a garden

items.synopsis: While the UK prime minister says his country alone cannot supply Ukraine with fighter jets, he pledges to support Volodymyr Zelenskyy in the creation of a "jets coalition" between allies.

title.children: UK and Ukraine working towards 'jets coalition' as Russia claims downing of Storm Shadow missile

image.altText: A skate lying on the seabed.

items.synopsis: Researchers say Tanya Plibersek's pledge of no new extinctions is under serious threat as the only known population of an endangered ancient Tasmania ray continues to nose dive.

title.children: Plibersek's pledge for no new extinctions on thin ice as endemic Tasmanian ray population plummets

image.altText: Aerial view of a small grey humpback calf laying on top of the the head of a large black humpback whale in clear bright blue wa

items.synopsis: Ningaloo's sparkling turquoise waters and whale sharks are well known to many, but this World Heritage treasure extends to the land, too - and conservationists fear for its future.

title.children: Ningaloo is a World Heritage treasure, but there are fears it will one day be paradise lost

image.altText: a man standing outdoors on a paddock with cows behind him and wearing a cap and looking out over the land

items.synopsis: NSW farmer Alastair McLaren has lost hundreds of thousands of dollars due to contamination from PFAS chemicals, but he's not one of the 30,000 people who will be compensated.

title.children: Alastair lost his business due to pollution from toxic foam — but he won't get a cent from a class action payout

image.altText: A man smiles with two others while posing for a selfie on stage in front of a large crowd.

items.synopsis: Thai voters have rejected the junta and its successors, instead looking set to vote in Thailand's most progressive party, Move Forward. But the election doesn't guarantee Thailand's opposition forces will be able to form government, writes Gregory Raymond.

title.children: Thailand is on the verge of a new democratic spring, but obstacles could be ahead

image.altText: Black and white photo of man with fuzzy black hair and a jumper.

items.synopsis: The British post-punk band has many dedicated older female fans, but their fandom is not about fancying lead singer Robert Smith. It's much more interesting.

title.children: Tattoos and erotic fan fiction; camaraderie and catharsis: Why The Cure fans are so devoted to the band

image.altText: A sign shows a red scull and bones and reads "contaminated".

items.synopsis: Residents are calling for more compensation after the Commonwealth stopped short of admitting liability in a class action settlement that will see $132.7 million split among 30,000 claimants.

title.children: 'They've gotten away with murder': $132.7m payout from Commonwealth over toxic PFAS

image.altText: A grey card with the PTV and myki symbols is placed against a card reader which says the card has expired.

items.synopsis: It's the end of the line for many physical myki cards, with Victorian commuters to be able to pay for public transport with their debit and credit cards in trials starting in 2024.

title.children: Physical myki cards to tap out as Victoria gives ticketing contract to new company

image.altText: Jasmina, woman in pink shirt smiling, holding a baby wearing a blue shirt.

items.synopsis: Michelle and Jono Harley always dreamed of having a family — their devastating fertility journey took a twist when relatives stepped in with an extraordinary backup plan.

title.children: Jasmina was 52 when she gave birth to her grandson. Now her daughter has her dream family

image.altText: The sea turbulent charges towards a beach beneath a threatening sky.

items.synopsis: Police have located a body in the search for a diver who went missing off Gellibrand Lower, in Victoria's south-west, last month.

title.children: Body found in search for missing diver off Victorian coast

image.altText: Female doctor wearing blue top and jacket in an office. Her hair is close-cropped and she wears glasses.

items.synopsis: Celebrity endorsements and social media influencers are helping drive more women to freeze their eggs. But one doctor is warning young women to seriously consider the financial, physical and emotional toll.

title.children: 'Don't jump into this': Women warned about egg freezing

image.altText: A composite of images of a young and old Mick Doleman and a shipwreck under the ocean.

items.synopsis: The wreck of the Blythe Star is located almost 50 years after it sank off the Tasmanian coast, its crew believed dead — until, astonishingly, they appeared out of the bush far from where the ship sank.

title.children: The crew of the Blythe Star were thought lost at sea. So why did they stumble out of a forest?

image.altText: Yevgeny Prigozhin leaves a cemetery. He is bald and stares at the camera from a distance.

items.synopsis: Yevgeny Prigozhin offered to reveal the position of Russian troops to the Ukrainian government, the Washington Post reports, citing leaked US intelligence documents.

title.children: Wagner head reportedly offered to reveal Russian troop locations to Ukraine

image.altText: A young girl smiles while looking up towards the camera wearing a backpack.

items.synopsis: The mother of Cleo Smith, Ellie Smith, says her family remains angry and heartbroken after the sentencing of the man who snatched her five-year-old daughter from a remote WA campsite.

title.children: 'Someone's tied our child, someone's hurt our kid': Family of Cleo Smith still angry over 'disgusting' kidnapping

image.altText: people standing outside an apartment block waiting to view it as a rent sign stands on the footpath

items.synopsis: The tax office says it is cracking down on landlords who are over-claiming tax deductions.

title.children: Tax Office's warning on landlord deductions, capital gains tax risk for Airbnb operators

image.altText: A woman and a man near Ayers Rock in Northern territory.

items.synopsis: Julie Schutt, who was missing in regional South Australia for a week, had not had any food or water in all the time she was missing, her brother says.

title.children: 'She was on her last legs': Missing Queensland woman was making way to a farmhouse when she was found

image.altText: A fire truck traverses a dirt track in rugged bushland.

items.synopsis: Country Fire Authority brigades in regional and rural Victoria say they are desperate for new members and that response times are being compromised in some areas.

title.children: Firefighter shortage creates 'high-risk situation' as country crews miss call-outs

image.altText: Online scam

items.synopsis: A national anti-scams centre is being established to help combat scams and online fraud, after Australians reported losing billions of dollars to fraudsters last year.

title.children: Government reveals details of $58m anti-scams centre, with expert 'hit squads' targeting fraudsters

image.altText: The first man has a tattoos on his face, the middle dark hair and beard, the third has receding dark hair & a moustache.

items.synopsis: A major manhunt is underway for a man who disappeared from the rural, low-security Palen Creek Correctional Centre with two other men yesterday afternoon.

title.children: 'Do not approach them': Police capture two men after trio escape Queensland prison

image.altText: A man with fair hair and skin, wearing a suit jacket and an open-necked shirt.

items.synopsis: A former fly-in fly-out worker is found guilty of raping a colleague at a remote mine site in WA, in a case that came to the public's attention amid wide-ranging allegations of sexual assaults and harassment within the mining industry.

title.children: Victim's family sob in court as FIFO worker found guilty of raping colleague at remote mine site

image.altText: A man wearing a suit looks at the camera

items.synopsis: Bruce Lehrmann's defence barrister Steve Whybrow tells an inquiry into the case that he was angered by the suggestion he colluded with Senator Linda Reynolds during the trial.

title.children: Bruce Lehrmann's barrister 'pissed off' over prosecutor's claims he colluded with Linda Reynolds during trial

image.altText: Fish floating in water

items.synopsis: NSW's chief scientist is aware his team will need to overcome distrust from some Menindee locals as it begins a review into the cause behind a mass fish kill in the Darling River during March.

title.children: NSW's chief scientist begins review into Menindee's mass fish kill that left about 20 million native species dead

image.altText: An older white man in heavily armoured combat gear and a helmet stands on a rooftop, with a soldier looking out behind him.

items.synopsis: Today, as Russia's President Vladimir Putin flails around dispatching one failed military chief after another, Yevgeny Prigozhin — for the moment at least — is probably the safest Russian in the world, writes John Lyons in Kyiv.

title.children: Putin needs this man more than anyone else — until the moment he ceases to be of use

image.altText: Sam Kerr squats behind the Women's FA Cup while holding the Australian flag and wearing her Chelsea jersey.

items.synopsis: The Matildas captain scores in Chelsea's 1-0 win over Manchester United, making her the outright most successful Australian footballer ever.

title.children: In a game of big moments, Sam Kerr's small glories set her apart

image.altText: Two sawfish lie dead on a sandy bank with their saws, also known as rostrums, cut off.

items.synopsis: An aquatic ecosystems expert at Murdoch University compares the "illegal" and "cruel" killing of four fish to poaching rhinos and elephants for their ivory.

title.children: Critically endangered sawfish likely killed for saw trophies, marine professor says

image.altText: A portrait shot of a smiling man in gold and black mayoral robes.

items.synopsis: Tasmanian mayor Danny Gibson resigns, saying "vile attacks" in media reports have taken a toll on his mental health and have become "a distraction from the important work of the City of Launceston".

title.children: Launceston Mayor Danny Gibson resigns following 'vile attacks, stemming from media reports'

image.altText: A composite image of three men. One in medical scrubs, two others in suits.

items.synopsis: Stuart Robert's resignation announcement has prompted high-profile candidates to chase Liberal Party pre-selection for his safe Gold Coast seat.

title.children: High-profile candidates put hands up for Liberal nomination in Fadden by-election

image.altText: A screenshot of a police body cam video of a car at the end of a dirt road

items.synopsis: The 31-year-old has been charged with breaking into a home and stabbing the occupant in the neck with a shovel before stealing their car.

title.children: Man charged over allegedly stabbing home invasion victim with shovel

image.altText: A herd of goat standing around in forestry

items.synopsis: In the southern Chilean city of Santa Juana, hit hard by wildfires earlier this year, locals have a special task force helping them fight blazes — and its members have four legs and horns.

title.children: Firefighting goats protecting Chilean forests from deadly blazes

image.altText: American flags are displayed together with Chinese flags on top of a trishaw in Beijing.

items.synopsis: Seventy-eight-year-old American passport holder and Hong Kong resident John Shing-wan Leung is sentenced to life imprisonment.

title.children: China jails US citizen for life on espionage charges

image.altText: Dominic Savage, Mia Threapleton and Kate Winslet pose while holding BAFTA awards. Threapleton and WInslet share a glance.

items.synopsis: Derry Girls, Bad Sisters, The Traitors and Paddington are among the big winners at the BAFTA TV Awards in London.

title.children: Kate Winslet wins big, alongside Queen Elizabeth II and Paddington at the BAFTA TV awards

image.altText: A woman smiling and holding a baby at a cafe

items.synopsis: Lawyers for a man charged over the alleged murder of Louise Hughes, who was found dead at a house in Adelaide's south-west, are calling for the charges to be dropped after an autopsy report showed inconclusive results.

title.children: Lawyers call for murder charges to be dropped after inconclusive autopsy report

image.altText: Rescue workers help an elderly woman to reach a makeshift shelter, guiding her up stairs as rain falls in the background.

items.synopsis: At least six people have died but the true impact of the disaster is not yet clear as the storm moves inland and weakens.

title.children: Powerful Cyclone Mocha floods homes in western Myanmar, at least 700 injured
